. _ _\nWABC (316) New Tork. Dance Or-]\nchestra.\n1:00 a. m. _\nKNX (337) Hollywood. Arnhelm\u2019s O\nchestra.\n(Copyright, 1927. by Audio Servlee,\nChicago.) i\nNight\nOrgan.\nBlack\nRADIO DISTRIBUTES\nNEWS TO RUSSIANS\nBy NEA Service\nWASHINGTON'. April 3.\u2014Russia\nis making: use of radio not only to\n?Ive listeners information but to\nsupply the country\u2019s leading news\npapers with daily news service.\nA description of the Russian\nradio news agency was given the\nAmerican Society of Newspaper\nt\u2019ditors in convention here By H. V.\n[Caltenborn of Brooklyn. X. V.\nFive times a day the agency,\nnamed Tass and located at Moscow,\n\u2022peaks news to 1G8 publishers In an\nirea that radiates 1,800 miles In all\ndirections.\nAn announcer with a musical,\nivell-modulated voice reads new* dis\npatches sent from the copy editor\u2019s\nleak. During the three and one\nhalf hours that Tass broadcasts\nibout 5,000 words are put on the air.\nTass has an absolute monopoly\npf all news, so there is no one to\n\u2022teal it. In addition, they own the\nlegal author\u2019* right to everything\n:hey transit.\nFor the convenience of listeners\nivho cannot read, a-radio newspaper,\ni summary of the important events\n:>f the day, is broadcast that eve-\nping. fl\nKaltehborn said that Tass\u2019s offl\n;ia!s have' found radio a great aid\n:o the people and also a help, in\njuilding newspaper circulation.\nON AIR FROM TO 19 f\nStation KYW, Chicago, operates a\nlix-hour program schedule five\nlights a week. Sunday and Monday\nire the two exception*. i\ns-i\\","height":"31960","width":"24564"}}
